If you're getting As and Bs it doesn't seem to me that your parents have anything justifiable to complain about. If it were me I'd probably throw my report card in their faces if they complained, and I'd go and buy a gamecard so they couldn't stop me. But that's me, and I had serious problems with my dad being overly controlling, so I sort of had my mom on my side usually...<br>
<br>
My dad actually had a huge beef with me being on the Internet at all, claiming I was tying up his phone line (at 2am!) and trying to restrict me to half an hour a day to check my email... so I went behind his back and had a second phone line installed. In my name. And on my dime. So there wasn't much he could do about it. He had nothing left to complain about. (Ironically, my dad decided to keep the line after I moved out, and had it transferred to my mom's name and they now use it for their own Internet access.)<br>
