<br>
I work at a hospital that has among other programs one that specializes in addictions.  A real addiction messes up your life. If you are missing school to play EQ, or turning down a chance to be with other friends to play EQ, or losing sleep because of the game your parents may have a valid concern.  If however it is something you fit into a balanced life they just being parents.<br>
<br>
Just always be honest with yourself, and your parents, and keep your priorities straight.  <br>
