<br>
Talk to your parents.<br>
<br>
No, seriously. Not just a in passing, not just when they pick you up from school, but make the time, please, and sit down and talk. Eat dinner with them, not in front of the computer, and use that time to talk about what's going on. ( Something my brother has yet to take my advice on /sigh ) More than anything I think opening up that communication with your parents will help you earn their trust to let you play. As others have a said, be honest, let them know  your intentions. I'm not sure if your parents play games or not but heck, it can't hurt to show them the game, make them make newbies and show them what it's about. I did just that with my father when I started playing online MUSHes when I was 15 or so and it helped because he knew what I was doing when I was online.<br>
<br>
You seem like a well spoken guy, and I know at that age it's hard to talk to the 'rents without getting into a shouting match but I think the effort is worth the reward.<br>
<br>
I also think that those folks that suggested you offer to pay ( or do chores to earn the $ to pay ) your own $12 a month are totally correct. Or you could solve both the grades and the cash issue by working out a deal with your parents where if you get a certain grade that = a certain amount of cash that goes to pay for your EQ, or make it that = a certain # of hours you get to play for. Comprimise with them. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
